<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-02T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="510" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24591/20: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-02T16:00:00-04:00">December
                                    2, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>612. War Department states that it has no objection to deletion of the
                            expression quoted in first paragraph of your telegram no. 1082, November
                            30, 6 p.m., and you are authorized to delete it.</p>
                        <pb facs="0496" n="484" xml:id="pg_484"/>
                        <p>You are also authorized to conclude an agreement with the Iranian
                            Government regarding jurisdiction in criminal cases of American troops
                            in Iran, provided such agreement is acceptable to General Connolly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>